"msg":"其實佢宣佈左有咩特別？係咪宣佈左進入之後就有啲咩特定政策要做？"},{"pid":"c4729e21695272af16cd4eec475a31b5a22fefda","tid":1920791,"uid":244649,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"50e1f905f438b59f41bdb90ff18e01746dd19b52","tid":1920791,"uid":172092,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-03-11T16:55:28.000Z","msg":"其實佢宣佈左有咩特別？係咪宣佈左進入之後就有啲咩特定政策要做？"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-03-11T19:15:05.000Z","msg":"Now the WHO has declared covid-19 a pandemic, what will it mean for the way the outbreak is treated and prepared for?<br />\n<br />\nThe WHO has stressed that using the word &ldquo;pandemic&rdquo; does not signal a change in its advice. It is still urging countries to &ldquo;detect, test, treat, isolate, trace and mobilise their people&rdquo;.<br />\nDr Nathalie MacDermott, National Institute for Health Research academic clinical lecturer King&rsquo;s College London, says: &ldquo;The change of term does not alter anything practically as the world has been advised for the last few weeks to prepare for a potential pandemic, which has hopefully been taken seriously by all countries.<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n係無架"}]}